author: CNN
description: “I” storms carry a notorious legacy. From Ivan to Ike to Ida, they’ve been some of the most destructive hurricanes in history -- and "Imelda" is the next name on the 2025 list. #cnn #news
title: Imelda will be in notorious company

author: CNN
description: The criminal charges against James Comey are historic, but President Trump suggested he may not be the only political foe facing indictment. Speaking today, Trump implied others could soon be targeted, following Comey’s indictment just days after Trump pushed for his prosecution and ousted the prosecutor who resisted. The move is seen as a striking effort to go after his perceived political enemies.   #CNN #News
title: Comey faces charges of lying to Congress, obstruction of justice

author: CNN
description: A travel blogger captured drone footage of a group of polar bears making themselves at home at an abandoned Soviet polar research facility in Russia.
title: Polar bears move into abandoned Soviet research station

author: CNN
description: A new CNN poll of independents shatters the myth of the classic swing voter who may go back and forth between political parties each election. CNN’s Jeff Zeleny breaks down the results and explains why independents are still one of the most important wildcards in American politics. #cnn #cnnnews
title: Why independent voters matter

author: CNN
description: Immigration authorities say an ICE officer has been relieved of his current duties after he was caught on video shoving a woman into a wall and pushing her to the ground. The incident occurred inside an immigration courthouse in New York yesterday. CNN's Gloria Pazmino reports.   #CNN #News
title: ICE officer relieved of duty after shoving incident

author: CNN
description: Former Director James Comey is the subject of an episode in a forthcoming CNN Original Series that will explore the opaque, complex, and high stakes relationship between FBI Directors and Presidents of the United States. As part of his participation in the CNN Original Series, Comey sat down with CNN on May 22, 2025 for a wide-ranging interview about his relationship with President Trump, his infamous firing and the legacy of the FBI.
title: Comey: Trump 'can't get over' me

author: CNN
description:
Redistricting battles are heating up ahead of the midterms. Republicans are pushing new maps in North Carolina, Texas, Ohio, Florida, Nebraska, Missouri, Kansas and Indiana, potentially adding multiple seats. Democrats could gain in California, Illinois, Maryland and Utah, where a judge ordered a map redraw. With control of Congress at stake, every seat will count. 

CNN’s Manu Raju was joined by CNN special correspondent Jamie Gangel, Bloomberg White House correspondent Catherine Lucey, and Wall Street Journal political investigations reporter Josh Dawsey for an in-depth discussion.   #CNN #News
title: More states move toward gerrymandering ahead of midterms

author: CNN
description: After Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu delivered a speech at the UN General Assembly, CNN's Oren Liebermann breaks down what stood out to him.
title: CNN breaks down Netanyahu's UN speech

author: CNN
description: Each fall, rangers at Alaska’s Katmai National Park track brown bears’ weight gain to see who’s best prepared for hibernation. But the contest isn’t just about pounds—it seeks the bear that “best exemplifies fatness and success,” according to the park.   #CNN #News
title: Need a pick-me-up? Fat Bear Week 2025 has you covered

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump told reporters "there will be others" after the former FBI Director James Comey was indicted. He said it was about justice, not revenge, as he departed the White House for the Ryder Cup in New York.
title: Trump says ‘there will be others’ prosecuted after Comey

author: CNN
description:
An Immigration and Customs Enforcement agent who was seen pushing a woman to the floor at a New York immigration courthouse has been "relieved of his current duties," according to ICE. The woman was pleading with the agent after a man, reportedly her husband, had been detained.

#CNN #News #ICE #NewYork
title: ICE agent shoves woman to ground in courthouse

author: CNN
description: Hundreds of US generals and admirals have been ordered to Quantico, Virginia, for a sudden meeting with Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth next Tuesday, officials told CNN. The reason remains unclear, even to many of the officers attending.   #CNN #News
title: Hegseth calls hundreds of top officers to Virginia in rare move

author: CNN
description: Presumed dead after an Israeli tank shell destroyed his jaw, 15-year-old Majd was placed in a morgue in Gaza before doctors noticed he was still alive. His mother fought for weeks to get him out, leaving two sons behind. CNN’s Christina Macfarlane met him in London before a team of surgeons attempted a radical reconstruction using bone and tissue from his leg. #cnn #news #shorts
title: From the Morgue to the Operating Room: Majd’s Fight to Smile Again

author: CNN
description: Lorenz Kraus said he killed his elderly parents in an interview with CNN affiliate WRGB. Following the interview, he was taken into custody outside of WRGB's building. Lorenz has been charged with two counts of 2nd degree murder and two counts of concealment of a human corpse. He pleaded not guilty and is being held without bail. #cnn #news
title: Man admits to killing parents during TV interview

author: CNN
description: Hurricane Helene made landfall in late September, 2024, killing at least 250 people in the United States. CNN's Isabel Rosales visits one of the hardest-hit areas, Asheville, North Carolina, to see what it looks like one year later.
title: 'Frozen in time': one year after Hurricane Helene

author: CNN
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu told the UN General Assembly he would “finish the job” of eliminating Hamas in Gaza, prompting scores of delegates to walk out before his speech, which was also broadcast along the Gaza border as part of what his office called a “public diplomacy effort.” He is set to meet President Trump on Monday, as Trump vows to block any Israeli annexation of the West Bank following recent US-Arab peace talks. #CNN #News
title: Netanyahu stands by Israel’s military actions in UN address

author: CNN
description: New surveillance video obtained by ABC News shows Immigration and Customs Enforcement agents and detainees taking cover as shots are fired at the detention center in Dallas. One detainee is dead and two more are in critical condition following the shooting, according to the Department of Homeland Security. #cnn #news
title: Surveillance video shows chaos inside ICE detention facility as shots ring out

author: CNN
description: As Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu walked to the podium to deliver his address at the UN General Assembly, dozens walked out. #un #netanyahu #walkout
title: Dozens walk out of UN as Netanyahu speaks

author: CNN
description:
In a wide-ranging interview, CNN’s Jeremy Diamond presses senior Hamas official, Ghazi Hamad, on his responsibility for Palestinians suffering in Gaza, and the tens of thousands killed following Hamas’ attack on Israel on October 7, 2023. He describes surviving an Israeli missile strike on Hamas leadership in Qatar and was challenged on the latest peace proposal. 
#cnn  #News
title: Watch extended cut of CNN's interview with Hamas official

author: CNN
description: Berlin's oldest queer nightclub, SchwuZ, has filed for bankruptcy. But closing will mean more than a party hotspot closing. It will mean the death of a community space that has been the cornerstone of Berlin's queer nightlife for decades.
title: Why Berlin's famed club scene is dying

author: CNN
description: President Trump's unprecedented intervention in former FBI Director James Comey's case has presidential historian Tim Naftali comparing the first Trump administration with the second. Naftali says the difference this time is that Trump is turning his words into actions and major changes are happening. #CNN #News
title: Historian reacts to Comey indictment: This isn't just red meat, these are orders

author: CNN
description: Kamala Harris said the situation in Gaza is "outrageous and it breaks my heart" as protesters interrupted the former vice president during an event promoting her new book in New York on Wednesday. #cnn #kamalaharris #gaza
title: Kamala Harris responds to pro-Palestinian protestors at book event

author: CNN
description:
Dr. Sanjay Gupta and neuroscientist Baroness Susan Greenfield, Oxford University professor and author of “Mind Change: How Digital Technologies Are Leaving Their Mark on Our Brains,” discuss how screen time might be impacting our human connections and own cognitive abilities. Greenfield also gives us three ways to reclaim our digital independence.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's Chasing Life podcast: http://swap.fm/l/clyt092625

#cnn #news #digital #technology #digitallife
title: How to use technology and not lose our minds | Chasing Life

title: CNN challenges Hamas leader about state of Israeli hostages

description: Former FBI Director James Comey has been indicted by a federal grand jury, an extraordinary escalation in President Donald Trump’s effort to prosecute his political enemies. CNN’s Kaitlan Collins and Evan Perez report. #CNN #News
title: Former FBI Director James Comey indicted

description: Former FBI Director James Comey has responded after a federal grand jury indicted him this evening. The indictment comes as President Donald Trump advances his efforts to prosecute his political foes.
title: Comey releases video reacting to indictment

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump is demanding an investigation following what he described as a “triple sabotage” during his visit to the United Nations General Assembly on Tuesday, taking to social media to claim that a series of technical mishaps, involving a stopped escalator, a teleprompter failure and audio issues, were deliberate acts meant to undermine him.
title: The blame game over Trump's escalator and prompter hiccup at UN

author: CNN
description: Former FBI Director James Comey has been indicted by a federal grand jury, an extraordinary escalation in President Donald Trump’s effort to prosecute his political enemies. James Comey and his lawyers have not commented yet.
title: Former FBI Director James Comey indicted

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump signed an executive action to impose a $100,000 application fee for H-1B visas in an effort to curb what his administration says is overuse of the program.
title: Trump admin cracks down on legal immigration
